# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
The issue is caused by package @angular/angular


### Description
When using matrix route optional parameters if the route absolute path consists in multiple paths with matrix parameters, the ActivatedRoute only contains the parameters of the last path. On the other side, if the path is composed by children routes and the main route doesn't have a component associated, then both all the matrix params will merge and doesn't respect its namespace.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
For example.

I define the following routes:

```
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    redirectTo: 'one',
    pathMatch: 'full'
  },
  {
    path: 'One',
    component: OneComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'two/test',
    component: TwoComponent
  }
];
```
Then, in OneComponent I have this function that I call in a button click event:

```
goToTwo() {
    this.router.navigate(['/two/', {twoMatrix: 'twoMatrixValue'}, 'test', {testMatrix: 'testMatrixValue'}]);
}
```
In TwoComponent:

```
ngOnInit() {
    this.activatedRoute.params.subscribe(values => {
      console.log(values);
    });
}
```
When I click the button and I go to TwoComponent the URL becames into:

`http://localhost:4200/two;twoMatrix=twoMatrixValue/test;testMatrix=testMatrixValue`

But when I print the activatedRoute params, only the matrix params related with the last path (test) are retrieved. It shows like this:

`{testMatrix: "testMatrixValue"}`

I expect that the params related with "two" will be also retrieved and printed.

I was testing with another routes configuration, for example:

```
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    redirectTo: 'one',
    pathMatch: 'full'
  },
  {
    path: 'one',
    component: OneComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'two',
    children: [
      {
        path: 'test',
        component: TwoComponent
      }
    ]
  }
];
```
With this children route, it works as expected. I am be able to retrieve all the parameters from this.activatedRoute.params.

But when I change this routes to this:
```
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    redirectTo: 'one',
    pathMatch: 'full'
  },
  {
    path: 'one',
    component: OneComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'two',
    component: TwoComponent,
    children: [
      {
        path: 'test',
        component: TwoComponent
      }
    ]
  }
];
```
This way, TwoComponent prints its parameters in its corresponding path. This requires two `router-outlet`. Without component attribute in two path ActivatedRoute populates its paramsMap with both of `testMatrix` and `twoMatrix`. This behaviour has a downside, because if both of params have the same name, one will override the other. With this attribute the first TwoComponent will print `twoMatrix` and the second one `testMatrix`.

The other solution I've found to get all the params is by using the URL of the activatedRoute this.activatedRoute.snapshot.url[0].parameterMap

The final question is, why can't I retrieve the parameters with the first route configuration? I suspect that is because the route two/test acts as whole, but I am not sure. Is this a bug?

Thanks in advance.














